# Security

## LightRAG + projection data access

LightRAG replaces Text2Cypher. Queries go through `aquery(..., only_need_context=True)` — the model never generates Cypher against the UI graph.

- **RAG Postgres (AGE + pgvector):** the agent role is **read/write**. LightRAG's query path writes an LLM/response cache into `PGKVStorage`; ingestion also writes all four stores. Do not use a read-only role for this database.
- **Supabase UI projection** (`movies`, `people`, `genres`, `acted_in`, `in_genre`): the backend reads over `SUPABASE_DB_URL` as the privileged `postgres` role (bypasses RLS). **Projection enforcement is the `/graph` (and chat) auth dependency**, not RLS. Keep RLS enabled with an `authenticated` SELECT policy anyway — that closes the PostgREST/Data API path and satisfies advisors.
- Fail closed on empty retrieval: never invent movie facts when both `movie:{id}` recovery and the title fallback find nothing.

## Secrets & auth

- Compare secrets with `hmac.compare_digest`, never `==`.
- Every non-public route requires an auth dependency (Supabase JWT). No unauthenticated data/LLM endpoints.
- Never log secrets or PII; sanitize user-derived strings before logging.

## LLM calls

- Always pass `timeout=` and `max_tokens=` (read from settings). No unbounded calls.

## Transport & config

- CORS: explicit origin allowlist. Never `allow_origins=["*"]` with `allow_credentials=True`. Fail fast if origins unset in prod.
- Validate required env vars at startup; refuse to boot on missing/placeholder values.
- Global exception handler returns a generic body (`{"detail": "Internal server error"}`) + a `request_id`; never return `str(exc)`.
